		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Quite a few people who read <a href="http://developers.slashdot.org/story/12/02/07/0043241/hacking-the-nes-with-lisp" class="postlink">the Slashdot story about this project</a> left comments amounting to "Why not put a whole computer on the NES cartridge board and have it fill a frame buffer that the PPU reads?" They were saying pretty much the same thing I've been saying for years whenever the idea of a "super-mapper" comes up: make a TV tuner cartridge and plug a Wii or a modern smartphone into it.

		

